Commit Message: Modify TcpSourceSink to auto-reconnect / restart the TCP client / server after the connection has been broken.
Use str() instead of decode() to avoid exception when bytes are not utf-8.

Revisit the reconnection for TcpSourceSink when it is a TCP server.

Instead of creating a new server socket, re-use the existing one. This also avoids socket-already-in-use errors in case the socket is not immediately released before attempting to create a new server socket.

Initial support for REST Source nodes.

The provided node is a Source that uses Flask to accept a string of byte values and send those bytes to all subscribing nodes.
Update the example to also make use of the RestService node.
Make the TCP reconnection more robust. Remove functionality from the base REST API node. Add some comments.
Update the readme file and restructure to enable PyPI package creation.
